  "prompt": "What colours complement amber?",
  "response": "Amber is a warm, vibrant color that sits between yellow and orange on the color wheel. To complement amber, you can consider using the following colors:\n\n1. **Teal or Turquoise**: These shades are opposite amber on the color wheel, making them complementary colors. They provide a striking contrast and can make amber stand out.\n\n2. **Navy Blue**: Dark blues offer a sophisticated contrast to amber, helping to balance its warmth.\n\n3. **Forest Green**: This earthy green tone works well with amber, creating a natural, harmonious look.\n\n4. **Deep Purple**: This color creates a rich, luxurious combination while enhancing the vibrancy of amber.\n\n5. **Burgundy or Maroon**: These deep red hues complement amber by providing a warm yet contrasting backdrop.\n\n6. **Charcoal Gray**: This neutral color offers a sleek and modern contrast to amber, allowing it to pop without overwhelming it.\n\nWhen using these complementary colors, you can adjust the balance to create the desired mood or effect, whether it\u2019s a bold statement or a more subtle, cohesive design.",
